About IBM CP Demo Framework

Welcome to IBM CP Demo Framework!

IBM CP Demo Framework is a turnkey solution for you to test drive software.
The browser-based, No-Code, Low-Code sandbox enables developers to try new technologies, whether you are trying to extend your application stack or building new skills.

With the CP Demo Framework, you can

1. Discover and try applications built on IBM and IBM Partner Technologies in real time.
2. Work with applications built on APIs, IBM Cloud services, IBM Watson service and more.
3. Modify code and export your work to your Git repository. The instructions can be found in the FAQs.

The IBM Developer Sandbox includes an IDE plugin, a code editor window, interactive ReadME files, and applications you can test.


CP Demo Framework IDE Plugin.

The CP Demo Framework IDE Plugin is on the left side of the screen. It is opened by default when you launch the sandbox and contains the navigation panel to navigate across applications supported on the sandbox.

The navigation panel contains three sections

1. Explore Applications: This section displays the application that was launched from the homepage or API Hub.
3. Featured Applications: This section displays the featured applications.
4. History: This section displays up to five previously launched applications by the user in previous sessions.


Code editor window.

The code editor window occupies the center section of the CP Demo Framework IDE plugin. The interactive README for the selected application is displayed here. Sample application code and sample code snippets for API-based applications open as new tabs in the code editor window.

The final section of the Code Editor Window is the debugging section and displays the relevant troubleshooting information when running a sample application.


Launching interactive README file for selected applications.

Launching the CP Demo Framework loads an interactive README in the code editor window for the selected application. You can launch the interactive README for any of the applications by hovering over the API product name and selecting the document icon. The interactive README files are built using the Didact framework.


About the Didact framework.

The Didact framework instructs users in a useful way about how to complete tasks through a combination of text (Markdown-or AsciiDoc-formatted), images, and active links that show VS Code functionality in action. Those links are paired with VS Code's simple command framework to interact with the IDE directly and that provides one-click access to nearly all the functionality VS Code and its extensions have to offer.


Executing code snippets for API endpoints.

Selecting an API endpoint for API base application will populate the sample code snippet for it in the code editor window in a new tab. Hovering on an API endpoint will show an execute icon. Selecting it will execute the sample generated code for the API endpoint in a new tab in the code editor window.
